latestPosts.caption:
✨NEW spin on Hot Pot @datang_official featuring their BRAND NEW Wok Fried DIY Dry Pot station ✨

📍8140 Leslie Rd, Richmond 

If you’re not a soup fan and your friends constantly crave hot pot this NEW Dry Pot Is for you! Just like their classic DIY hot pot you choose and weigh your ingredients. They have a NEW section called Wok Fried where you can pick for your dry pot and there’s items that are better suited for wok fried like wings, squid, chicken cartilage, spare ribs and more! 

Their Chicken Laksa soup option is delicious if  you wan go classic hot pot. Not to be missed is their Sweet & Sour Pork which is not classic but I loved how crunchy it was and I preferred it not overly sauced. Ofc fresh 🍉 juice always hits the spot. 

✨Sauce bar and free soft serve (rotating flavours) are included with your meal. 
✨If you’re going with dry pot they recommend not choosing too many ingredients that release a lot of liquid so keep that in mind.

👽FREE admission to @metropolisatmet #summeratthemet Explore The Galaxy! 

The event invites shoppers into a multiverse of entertainment. With over 15 plus food vendors, live entertainment and so much more it’s fun for all ages. 

✨Event info: 
July 4th & 5th 2-10pm
July 6th 2-8pm
Located in the South Plaza Outdoor by Chipotle 
Free, 4-hour visitor parking available at the Met, along with easy SkyTrain access

Visitors can pop by Guest Services to obtain a Summer Passport (available now - Sept 1), which encourages exploration of the various Summer at the Met activations while collecting stamps along the way. After gathering seven stamps, guests receive a surprise gift, while those who collect 10 stamps are eligible for a chance to win a prize valued at $100.

Thank you @gatherpr_ & @metropolisatmet for putting on another amazing summer event!

✨BRAND NEW Pop Up Patio in Vancouver that will be your go to spot all summer long. @baesideco offers picturesque views of Vancouver’s skyline while you sip on amazing cocktails & delicious bites. 🍹☀️🍸 💃 

📍601 Stamps Landing in False Creek 

Bae Side officially open today and trust me they have some of the tastiest cocktails in the city. Their delicious food combines West Coast ingredients with global inspiration. 

Cocktails we tried that were Bartender’s 💋
✨Garden Fresh G&T (gin, cucumber, rosemary, mint, grapefruit, orange, lime, cranberry, rose, tonic water)
King & Marry (tequila, mango, lemon, rosemary)
✨Oh My Coco (white rum, coconut Malibu, coconut, lemon)
✨Garden Fresh G&T (gin, cucumber, rosemary, mint, grapefruit, orange, lime, cranberry, rose, tonic water)

The patio will operate all summer long before they transition inside for the Fall for another fun reveal. The space will become a NEW Restaurant Mishree on the Water once it’s fully renovated. 

👉Tag your bae and get your summer vibe started! 

Thank you @baesideco @wearevancouverpr @tarajarmstrong @chelle_lan for such a fun evening! Can’t wait to go back! 🥂

latestPosts.caption:
Wake Up Hot Lunch Set @banbuxian is ONLY $47.95 and generous enough to feed up to 4 people. (Burnaby location ONLY) 

If you love Szechuan cuisine this deal is made for you. It was mine and my parents first time @banbuxian and we loved our introduction to their food with this incredible deal. I was shocked at how spacious the space was with lots of semi private booths for you to enjoy with family & friends. 

Here’s what you get for $47.95 (Mon-Fri from 1130am to 230pm) 📍3665 Kingsway #110 

1️⃣Choose one cold dish:
• Spicy Crystal Noodles
• Spicy Cucumber ✨

2️⃣Choose one hot dish:
• Fish-Flavored Shredded Pork
• Fresh Pepper Chicken with Pork Intestines 
• Beef with Chili ✨

3️⃣Choose one vegetable dish
• Thai Pepper Shredded Potatoes
• Garlic Choy Sum ✨
• Scrambled Eggs with Tomatoes 

✨We were very happy with all of our choices. We especially loved how flavourful the beef was and that they also stir fried it not only with chilis but pickled peppers & lots of cilantro. If you have more than a few people I definitely recommend adding the Spicy Prawns.

📣BEST HOT POT DEAL! For ONLY $19.99/person @beijing_hotpotvan you get so much food that you’ll be packing it home to enjoy a second serving. 

From the pretty ambience to the quality not to mention quality of ingredients it exceeded our expectations. My dad & I seriously couldn’t belt how much meat they gave you for each set. They’re also VERY generous with their signature peanut sesame sauce that’s so good. You’ll wanna double dip (it’s your own so go ahead 😝) I highly recommend getting their plum juice which is so refreshing with hot pot.

Here’s what you get for $19.99 (available daily from 1130am to 430pm)
• Choose from 5 Broths (House, Sour & Spicy, White Pepper pork tripe, Tomato or Spicy)
• Pick your protein ( beef, lamb or combo)
• Mixed Seafood & Veggie Platter
• Hand cut Noodles
• Signature Sesame Peanut Sauce AND sauce bar is included 
✨Highly recommend their tomato broth!
